ANC headquarters Luthuli House in Sauer Street, Johannesburg, seen at dusk on 12 June 2013. JOHANNESBURG - The taxman has given the ANC an ultimatum to pay its overdue tax bill or have its assets attached. The governing party owes the South African Revenue Service just over R100-million. In December last year, SARS gave the ANC 10 days to pay up but three months later, it's failed to do so. READ | ANC salary crisis scandalous, says analyst eNCA has reliably learnt that this bill includes employees’ tax, UIF and other levies. The ANC was for months in a tug of war with its more than 300 employees over unpaid salaries. It eventually paid the staff at the beginning of last month.